# AR Mapping (Unity AR Foundation)

This repository contains a Unity project using **AR Foundation**, tested on **iPhone** with ARKit and Unityâ€™s AR template. It is designed to demonstrate or serve as a starting point for building augmented reality features using Unity's cross-platform AR solution.

> âš ï¸ **Disclaimer:** This repository is intended for personal use, version control, and development tracking. It is **not a ready-made template or starter kit**. Files may require configuration depending on your platform, device, or Unity setup.

---

## ğŸ§  What Is AR Foundation?

[AR Foundation](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.xr.arfoundation@latest) is a framework developed by Unity Technologies to allow cross-platform development of augmented reality experiences. It supports both ARKit (iOS) and ARCore (Android), letting you write once and deploy to both platforms (with some platform-specific configuration).



## ğŸ“± Supported Platforms

- iOS (tested on iPhone 12 and up)
- Android (with ARCore support)
- Unity Editor (limited preview/testing via AR Simulator)

> âš ï¸ iOS builds require Xcode and a valid Apple Developer profile to run on-device.

