## ğŸ§  YOLOv5 â†’ Unity Export Tool

This Unity project uses a lightweight YOLOv5 object detection model (e.g. for detecting doors in AR).  
To build and convert the trained `.pt` weights into `.onnx` format for Unity Barracuda:

From the root project directory (where this README lives), run:

```bash
bash yolov5/build_and_export_unity.sh

ğŸ¯ Training a Custom YOLOv5 Model

To train your own object detector (e.g., for detecting doors):

ğŸ“ 1. Prepare Your Dataset
Your dataset should follow the standard YOLO structure:

dataset/
â”œâ”€â”€ images/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ train/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ val/
â”œâ”€â”€ labels/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ train/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ val/
â””â”€â”€ data.yaml
Sample data.yaml:

train: ../images/train
val: ../images/val
nc: 1
names: ['door']
You can generate this format using Roboflow or manually.
ğŸ§  2. Train the Model
From the yolov5/ folder, run:

python train.py --img 320 --batch 16 --epochs 100 --data data.yaml --weights yolov5s.pt --name doors_yolov5s
After training, your weights will be saved at:

yolov5/runs/train/doors_yolov5s/weights/best.pt
ğŸ” 3. Export for Unity
From the root directory (3D UI/), simply run:

bash yolov5/build_and_export_unity.sh
The converted model will be available for use in Unity as a Barracuda NNModel.

ğŸ“š Resources

YOLOv5: https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5
Training Custom Data: YOLOv5 Wiki
Roboflow (Optional): https://roboflow.com/
Unity Barracuda Docs: https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.barracuda
ğŸ›  Unity Requirements

Unity 2022+ with AR Foundation + XR Plugin
Barracuda (ONNX inference runtime)
Prefabs scaled to real-world sizes (e.g. 1m wide door)
ARRaycastManager + ARPlaneManager properly configured in scene

